import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of x?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    color_counts = data['color'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=color_counts.index, y=color_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Color')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of colors?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(color_counts.index, title='Colors')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
